Assembler Architecture

* EIP: Program counter. Points to the next instruction to be executed.

* Registers: They are very frequently used as quick access variable.

* Condition codes:
    - They store information regarding the behavior of the last executed instruction.
    - They are used in coditional jumps.

* Memory:
    - Byte-addressable vector, Little Endian.
    - Code, user data, OS data
    - Stact to support subrutine management.
